'''genkernel''' is used to automate the build process of the [[kernel]] and [[initramfs]]. Some of the general features:
* configure the kernel sources
* build bzImage and copy to /boot
* create initramfs and copy to /boot
* create symlinks in /boot
* add custom content to initramfs for encryption, splash images, extra modules etc.
* compress initramfs
* configure the bootloader

== Installation ==
You can install {{Package|sys-kernel/genkernel}} with the following command:
{{Emerge|sys-kernel/genkernel}}

=== USE Flags ===
{{USEflag|package=sys-kernel/genkernel
|crypt++no+
|cryptsetup++no+
|ibm++no+
|selinux++no+
}}

== Configuration ==
The configuration file is {{Path|/etc/genkernel.conf}} and is very well documented.

